# UI Module

## Module Purpose and Responsibilities

The UI module (`PigeonLib/Pigeon/UI/`) provides a retained-mode, ECS-driven 2D user interface layer on top of the engine. Its responsibilities are:

- Maintaining a hierarchy of UI entities in the EnTT registry, each described by a `BaseComponent`.
- Resolving the world-space position and size of each element through recursive parent-child layout traversal.
- Processing mutation commands (resize, re-parent, enable/disable, texture swap, text update) that arrive as one-frame components, applying them to the underlying data components each frame.
- Loading entire UI trees from JSON layout files on demand.
- Destroying UI entities and their full subtrees on request.
- Performing hit-testing against the current mouse position each frame and emitting hover/click/release one-frame events.
- Translating enabled, visible UI entities into renderer in-frame events (`DrawUIQuadInFrameEvent`, `DrawUIStringInFrameEvent`) that are consumed downstream by `Renderer2DSystem`.

---

## How the UI Module Differs from Renderer2D

`Renderer2DSystem` is a **direct-draw** pipeline: game code emits `DrawQuadInFrameEvent` / `DrawSpriteInFrameEvent` / `DrawStringInFrameEvent` in-frame events and the renderer flushes them in the same frame. There is no persistent state for those elements between frames.

The UI module is **hierarchy-based and retained**: UI elements live as permanent ECS entities across frames. Their layout is computed from a parent/child chain stored in `BaseComponent::m_Parent`. Mutations are driven by one-frame command components rather than by direct component writes. The output of `UIRenderSystem` feeds `DrawUIQuadInFrameEvent` / `DrawUIStringInFrameEvent` in-frame events, which are then consumed by the same `Renderer2DSystem` flush — the two pipelines converge only at the renderer level.

The UI module also has its own fixed orthographic camera (`RendererConfigSingletonComponent`) with a 1920x1080 logical resolution, independent of the scene's `OrthographicCameraComponent`. This keeps UI coordinates stable regardless of the world camera.

---

## Parent/Child Entity Hierarchy

Each UI entity that has a `BaseComponent` is a node in the hierarchy. The relationship is expressed entirely through a single field:

```
BaseComponent::m_Parent  (entt::entity, entt::null = root)
```

There is no explicit children list stored on a parent. Child lookup is performed by scanning all `BaseComponent` entities and filtering on `m_Parent`. The helper `GetUIChildrenForElement` performs this linear scan.

Layout computation (`GetGlobalBoundsForElement` / `GetGlobalBoundsForElementParent`) is recursive: to resolve element E's world position, the algorithm first recurses up to the root to accumulate an origin rectangle, then applies E's own alignment and spacing on the way back down.

The `IsUIElementEnabled` helper also walks the chain upward: an element is considered disabled if any ancestor has `m_Enabled = false`.

---

## ECS Components

All components are declared in `UIComponents.h` under namespace `pg::ui`.

### `BaseComponent`

The mandatory component for every UI entity. Acts as layout metadata and the hierarchy link.

| Field | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `m_Size` | `glm::vec2` | Width and height of the element's bounding box in logical pixels. |
| `m_Spacing` | `glm::vec2` | Offset applied after horizontal/vertical alignment. |
| `m_HAlign` | `EHAlignType` | Horizontal anchor within the parent's bounds: `eLeft`, `eCenter`, `eRight`. |
| `m_VAlign` | `EVAlignType` | Vertical anchor within the parent's bounds: `eTop`, `eCenter`, `eBottom`. |
| `m_Parent` | `entt::entity` | Parent entity handle; `entt::null` for root elements. |
| `m_UUID` | `pg::UUID` | Stable identifier used for event targeting and hit-test reporting. |
| `m_Enabled` | `bool` | When `false`, the element and all its children are skipped by render and event systems. |

### `TextComponent`

Optional visual component for text-rendering elements. Must not coexist with `ImageComponent` on the same entity (enforced by the JSON loader).

| Field | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `m_FontID` | `pg::UUID` | UUID key into `ResourceMapSingletonComponent::m_FontMap`. Null UUID falls back to `EngineConfigSingletonComponent::m_DefaultFontID`. |
| `m_Text` | `std::string` | UTF-8 string to render. Newline characters split into multiple lines. |
| `m_Color` | `glm::vec4` | RGBA text color. Default is opaque black `(0,0,0,1)`. |
| `m_Kerning` | `float` | Inter-character spacing multiplier passed to the font. Default `1.0`. |
| `m_Spacing` | `float` | Line-spacing multiplier passed to the font. Default `1.0`. |

### `ImageComponent`

Optional visual component for texture-rendering elements. Must not coexist with `TextComponent` on the same entity.

| Field | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `m_TextureHandle` | `pg::UUID` | UUID key into `ResourceMapSingletonComponent::m_TextureMap`. |

### `RendererConfigSingletonComponent`

Singleton. Created automatically by `UIRenderSystem` on its first frame if absent.

| Field | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `m_Camera` | `pg::OrthographicCamera` | Fixed orthographic projection: left=0, right=1280, bottom=-720, top=0. |
| `m_Width` | `float` | Logical canvas width. Default `1920`. |
| `m_Height` | `float` | Logical canvas height. Default `1080`. |

### One-Frame Command Components

These are submitted by external systems to request mutations. `UIControlSystem` reads and applies them, then they are auto-removed by the ECS at end of the next frame.

| Component | Fields | Effect when applied |
|---|---|---|
| `UIUpdateTransformOneFrameComponent` | `m_Size`, `m_Spacing`, `m_HAlign`, `m_VAlign` | Overwrites the corresponding fields in `BaseComponent`. |
| `UIUpdateParentOneFrameComponent` | `m_Parent` | Sets `BaseComponent::m_Parent`. |
| `UIUpdateEnableOneFrameComponent` | `m_Enabled` | Sets `BaseComponent::m_Enabled`. |
| `UIUpdateUUIDOneFrameComponent` | `m_UUID` | Sets `BaseComponent::m_UUID`. |
| `UIUpdateImageUUIDOneFrameComponent` | `m_UUID` | Sets `ImageComponent::m_TextureHandle`. |
| `UIUpdateTextOneFrameComponent` | `m_FontID`, `m_Text`, `m_Color`, `m_Spacing`, `m_Kerning` | Overwrites all fields of `TextComponent`. |
| `UIDestroyOneFrameComponent` | `m_DUMMYVAR` (unused bool) | Recursively destroys the entity and all its children via `destroy_deferred`. |

### One-Frame Event: `LoadLayoutEvent`

| Field | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `m_UUID` | `pg::UUID` | UUID key into `ResourceMapSingletonComponent::m_UILayoutMap` identifying the JSON layout file to load. |

Emitted via `accessor.EmplaceEvent<LoadLayoutEvent>(...)`, which creates an ephemeral ECS entity tagged with `EventComponent` and `LoadLayoutEvent`. `UIControlSystem` reads it the next frame via `view<LoadLayoutEvent>()` and destroys it via `ClearEvents()` at the end of that frame.

### One-Frame Output Events (from `UIEventSystem`)

These are emitted on the entity that was interacted with and carry the UUID of that element.

| Component | Field | Trigger |
|---|---|---|
| `UIOnHoverOneFrameComponent` | `m_ElementID` | Mouse position is inside the element's world bounds. |
| `UIOnClickOneFrameComponent` | `m_ElementID` | `PG_MOUSE_BUTTON_LEFT` is in `InputStateSingletonComponent::m_KeysPressed` while hovering. |
| `UIOnReleaseOneFrameComponent` | `m_ElementID` | `PG_MOUSE_BUTTON_LEFT` is in `InputStateSingletonComponent::m_KeysReleased` while hovering. |

