## Public API

There is no free-function creation API. All UI manipulation goes through ECS operations on the world registry. The publicly usable surface is:

### Creating a UI element (programmatically)

```cpp
entt::entity ent = accessor.create();

pg::ui::BaseComponent base;
base.m_Size    = { 200.f, 100.f };
base.m_Spacing = { 10.f,  10.f  };
base.m_HAlign  = pg::ui::EHAlignType::eLeft;
base.m_VAlign  = pg::ui::EVAlignType::eTop;
base.m_Parent  = parentEntity;   // entt::null for root
base.m_UUID    = pg::UUID::Generate();
base.m_Enabled = true;
accessor.emplace_deferred<pg::ui::BaseComponent>(ent, std::move(base));

// Add one visual component (image or text, not both):
pg::ui::ImageComponent img;
img.m_TextureHandle = textureUUID;
accessor.emplace_deferred<pg::ui::ImageComponent>(ent, std::move(img));
```

### Loading a layout from a JSON file

```cpp
pg::ui::LoadLayoutEvent event;
event.m_UUID = layoutUUID;   // must be registered in ResourceMapSingletonComponent::m_UILayoutMap
accessor.EmplaceEvent<pg::ui::LoadLayoutEvent>(std::move(event));
```

`UIControlSystem` processes this event on the next frame and creates all entities.

### Mutating an existing element

Attach the appropriate one-frame command component. `UIControlSystem` applies it next frame and removes it.

```cpp
// Resize and reposition:
pg::ui::UIUpdateTransformOneFrameComponent upd;
upd.m_Size    = { 300.f, 150.f };
upd.m_Spacing = { 5.f, 5.f };
upd.m_HAlign  = pg::ui::EHAlignType::eCenter;
upd.m_VAlign  = pg::ui::EVAlignType::eCenter;
accessor.emplace_oneframe<pg::ui::UIUpdateTransformOneFrameComponent>(ent, std::move(upd));

// Enable/disable:
pg::ui::UIUpdateEnableOneFrameComponent enUp;
enUp.m_Enabled = false;
accessor.emplace_oneframe<pg::ui::UIUpdateEnableOneFrameComponent>(ent, std::move(enUp));
```

### Destroying a UI subtree

```cpp
accessor.emplace_oneframe<pg::ui::UIDestroyOneFrameComponent>(rootEnt);
// Recursively destroys rootEnt and all entities whose m_Parent chain leads to rootEnt.
```

### Helper functions (`UIHelpers.h`)

| Function | Signature | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `GetGlobalBoundsForElement` | `(accessor, baseComp, renderComp, uiBoundsSize, level&) -> glm::vec4` | Returns `(x, y, w, h)` in logical pixels for a given element size. |
| `GetGlobalBoundsForElementParent` | `(accessor, baseComp, renderComp, level&) -> glm::vec4` | Returns the resolved bounding box of the element's parent. |
| `IsUIElementEnabled` | `(accessor, baseComp) -> bool` | Returns `true` only if the element and all ancestors are enabled. |
| `GetUIChildrenForElement` | `(accessor, entity) -> vector<entt::entity>` | Linear scan returning all entities whose `m_Parent == entity`. |

