## Data Flow Per Frame

```
Frame N
  ├── UIControlSystem::Update
  │     ├── Apply UIUpdateTransformOneFrameComponent  →  BaseComponent (write)
  │     ├── Apply UIUpdateParentOneFrameComponent     →  BaseComponent (write)
  │     ├── Apply UIUpdateEnableOneFrameComponent     →  BaseComponent (write)
  │     ├── Apply UIUpdateUUIDOneFrameComponent       →  BaseComponent (write)
  │     ├── Apply UIUpdateImageUUIDOneFrameComponent  →  ImageComponent (write)
  │     ├── Apply UIUpdateTextOneFrameComponent       →  TextComponent (write)
  │     ├── Process LoadLayoutEvent                   →  create BaseComponent/ImageComponent/TextComponent (deferred)
  │     └── Process UIDestroyOneFrameComponent        →  destroy_deferred entity + children
  │
  ├── UIEventSystem::Update
  │     └── Hit-test all BaseComponent entities       →  UIOnHoverOneFrameComponent
  │                                                      UIOnClickOneFrameComponent
  │                                                      UIOnReleaseOneFrameComponent
  │                                                      (emplace_oneframe on matching entities)
  │
  ├── UIRenderSystem::Update
  │     ├── Image pass: BaseComponent + ImageComponent  →  DrawUIQuadInFrameEvent (inframe)
  │     └── Text pass:  BaseComponent + TextComponent   →  DrawUIStringInFrameEvent (inframe)
  │
  └── Renderer2DSystem::Update
        └── Consumes DrawUIQuadInFrameEvent and DrawUIStringInFrameEvent
              →  batches into m_LayerBatchMap[level]
              →  GPU draw calls
```

Deferred adds from `UIControlSystem` (new entities from JSON load) become visible starting **Frame N+1**, not in the same frame they are requested.

