## Non-Obvious Design Decisions

**No explicit children list.** Parent relationships are stored only on children (`m_Parent`). Finding children requires a full linear scan of all `BaseComponent` entities. This keeps the data model simple at the cost of O(n) child lookup. It is only exercised during destroy and in the helper `GetUIChildrenForElement`, which is not called in the hot render path.

**Layout computed every frame, not cached.** `GetGlobalBoundsForElement` is called independently by both `UIEventSystem` and `UIRenderSystem` every frame for every entity. There is no dirty flag or cached world transform. This avoids a separate layout system and any invalidation logic, at the cost of redundant computation.

**Mutation through one-frame command components rather than direct writes.** External systems cannot write `BaseComponent` directly — only `UIControlSystem` holds `writeSet` access over it. All mutations arrive as one-frame command components, which enforces the "one writer per component" rule and makes the access graph unambiguous.

**`UIDestroyOneFrameComponent::m_DUMMYVAR`.** The field is unused. It exists solely to satisfy the engine rule that every component must have at least one data member (tag-only components are disallowed).

**`RendererConfigSingletonComponent` is auto-created.** `UIRenderSystem` creates it on its first `Update` call if absent. The first frame returns early after the deferred add; rendering begins from the second frame. This avoids requiring the application to manually instantiate the config singleton at startup.

**Level/Z encodes hierarchy depth.** `GetGlobalBoundsForElementParent` increments `level` by 1 per recursion step. That depth integer is placed into `transform[3][2]` (the Z translation). `Renderer2DSystem::DrawLayerBatch` extracts `int(transform[3][2])` and routes the quad into `m_LayerBatchMap[level]`. Layers 0–99 are flushed in ascending order, ensuring children (deeper nesting = higher level) render over parents without any explicit Z ordering by the caller.

**`UIOnClickOneFrameComponent` and `UIOnReleaseOneFrameComponent` are mutually exclusive per entity per frame.** The event system checks `m_KeysPressed` first and only checks `m_KeysReleased` in an else branch. A single frame cannot produce both a click and a release event for the same element.

**Font fallback in `UIRenderSystem`.** If `TextComponent::m_FontID` is null (default-constructed), the render system substitutes `EngineConfigSingletonComponent::m_DefaultFontID`. This allows text elements defined in JSON without an explicit `font` key to render using the engine's global default font.

**`uiFile` indirection in JSON.** A JSON element node can contain a `uiFile` key instead of a `ui` object. The loader reads the referenced file and parses it as a child of the current parent. This allows layouts to be composed from separate files.
